  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tzu Chi&#x2019;s relief action to the drought situation in Vietnam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ben Tre Province in Vietnam suffered a severe drought the whole year, leading the residents of two communities to lack access to clean water. Since July of 2017, volunteers of Taiwan Buddhist Tzu Chi Foundation have begun to distribute 500 horizontal water towers to help them.
Last year, Ben Tre Province suffered a severe drought, leading local residents to experience crop failure and the lack of tap water. After learning the news from local government, the volunteers have begun to distribute water towers since July of this year. In total, 500 families from two communities have received help.</narrative>
  </description>
